Input = minutes
rate = 0.15 (15 pences)
vat = 0.2 (20%)
Ouput = minutes * rate * vat + minutes * rate

Input             |     Excpet Ouput                             |          Ouput
Interger number   |     minutes * rate * vat + minutes * rate    |          minutes * rate * vat + minutes * rate
0                 |     0                                        |          0
1                 |     1 * 0.15 * 0.2 + 1 * 0.2 = 0.18          |          0.18
125               |     125 * 0.15 * 0.2 + 125 * 0.2 = 22.5      |          22.5
A                 |     Error                                    |          Error

Reason to test: number 0 and 1 is the most simple number that easily for us to see the smallest change so that we can understand when we input the larger number